@Kayla You bring up the hurricanes that have happened this season. Note the date on the graph. Also note that Hurricanes Helene and Milton were September 24 – 27, 2024 and October 5 – 10, 2024. How could there be so much drought with these major rain events?  

Please note that the way the level of drought is calculated is by comparing to a region’s area, not the country’s drought level.  

Go to U.S. Drought Monitor (www.drought.gov/data-maps-tools/us-drought-monitor) to learn more about how the level of drought is determined.

